The paper deals with optimization problems related to automated sortation centers, which involve assigning tasks to agents and finding collision-free paths for them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also deals with systems and control, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experimental results and showcases the benefits of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
